messages.subject: Re: [Unschooling-dotcom] Interesting Experiment
messages.msgSnippet: there should be a forward option on your email reader, hit this, scroll down until you find your slot and put your date in, then put the email addy(ies) in
messages.messageBody:
there should be a 'forward' option on your email reader, hit this, scroll down until you find your slot and put your date in, then put the email addy(ies) in the 'To' box.  HTH :-)
 
BTW, mine is Nov 25th :-)
 
Tracy

From: bctswim@...

messages.messageBody:
> > AN INTERESTING EXPERIMENT
> >
> > I thought you might enjoy being a part of this. Out of all of the
> > billions
> > of people that live in the world, there has got to be somebody born on
> > each
> > date of the year. To try to accomplish this task of seeing if we can
fill
> >
> > the calendar up with a birthday on every day of the year, add your birth
> > date to the list below. If your birth date is already listed, put a star
> > next to it! And then send this list to all of your friends, plus back to
> >
> > the person that sent it to you! Let's see if we can do it!!!!
> > (Remember, copying and pasting this to a NEW Email will keep it clean
and
> >
> > make it easier to read than just forwarding it. And PLEASE, delete the
> > names it has been sent from and to -no one wants to scroll down a list
of
> >
> > names to get to the message - Thanks! and Happy Birthday!
